name: Slow Cooker Turkey and Dumplings
author: Diana
summary: Great for that leftover turkey. Creamy comfort food on a cold day.
ingredients: 2 (10.75 ounce) cans  condensed cream of chicken soup
1 ½ cups chopped cooked turkey, or more to taste
1 cup chopped potatoes, or more to taste
1 cup chopped carrots, or more to taste
½ (10 ounce) can refrigerated buttermilk biscuit dough (such as Pillsbury Grands!®), cut into squares
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup, chicken broth, turkey, potatoes, carrots, onion, butter, garlic powder, and poultry seasoning together in a slow cooker
Cook on High for 3 hours; stir
Arrange biscuits atop turkey mixture and cook until biscuits are cooked through, about 1 more hour
